Press Release also attached
Union City, Calif. – On 12/20/25, the Union City Police Department will conduct a driving under the influence (DUI/DL) Checkpoint at an undisclosed location. 
DUI/DL checkpoint locations are determined based on data showing incidents of impaired driving-related crashes. The primary purpose of DUI/DL checkpoints are to promote public safety by taking suspected impaired drivers off the road.
“Impaired drivers put others on the road at significant risk,” Sgt. Steven Fong said. “Any prevention measures that reduce the number of impaired drivers on our roads significantly improve traffic safety.”
The Union City Police Department reminds the public that impaired driving is not just from alcohol. Some prescription medications and over-the-counter drugs may interfere with driving. While medicinal and recreational marijuana are legal, driving under the influence of marijuana is illegal.
Drivers charged with a first-time DUI face an average of $13,500 in fines and penalties, as well as a suspended license.
Funding for this program was provided by a grant from the California Office of Traffic Safety, through the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration.
For Traffic or specific grant-related questions, please contact: 
Traffic Sergeant Steven Fong
510-471-1365 (Main Line)
510-675-5221(Direct Line)
Stevenf@unioncity.org (Email)', '2025-12-05', '6pm-2am PST', 'https://www.facebook.com/unioncitypd/posts/union-city-police-department-holding-duidl-checkpoint-december-20-2025press-rele/1267994332020044/', '2025-12-04 08:42:06+00', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/S+Atlantic+Blvd+%26+W+Riggin+St,+Monterey+Park,+CA+91754,+USA/@34.0374555,-118.1472495,361m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m6!3m5!1s0x80c2cf90910380d3:0x3de54fcfc9accd39!8m2!3d34.0375007!4d-118.1463541!16s%2Fg%2F11f32gzgfx?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI2MDEyNS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D', '4cb96c6d-fb51-4a01-affb-cf263330254c'), ('4', 'CA', 'Alameda ', 'Pleasanton ', 'on Santa Rita Road between Rosewood Drive and Pimlinco Drive', 'DUI Checkpoint Planned for December 5
The Pleasanton Police Department will conduct a DUI checkpoint on Friday, December 5, on Santa Rita Road between Rosewood Drive and Pimlico Drive. The checkpoint will run from 6:00 p.m. to midnight.
DUI checkpoints help reduce impaired-driving crashes by raising awareness and removing impaired drivers from the road. During Friday’s operation, officers will be looking for signs of alcohol or drug impairment, including impairment caused by certain prescription medications or marijuana — especially when combined with other substances. Specially trained officers will be on scene to evaluate drivers suspected of being under the influence of drugs.
Driving under the influence has serious consequences: jail time, fines, DUI classes, license suspension, and other costs that can exceed $10,000.
Please plan ahead. Designate a sober driver or arrange another safe way home.
If you see a driver who appears impaired, call 911 immediately.
This checkpoint is funded by the California Highway Patrol Cannabis Tax Fund Grant Program.', '2025-12-05', '6pm-12am PST', 'https://www.facebook.com/PleasantonPoliceCA/posts/-dui-checkpoint-planned-for-december-5the-pleasanton-police-department-will-cond/1309730961183928/', '2025-12-04 08:47:10+00', null, 'ef7edfd2-e752-49da-b069-65f799618440'), ('5', 'CA', 'Alameda ', ' Union City', ' undisclosed location', 'Union City Police Department Holding DUI/DL Checkpoint December 20, 2025.
